    "Several hybrid stakeholders (e.g., payors, health care practitioners) perform diverse roles in the innovation eco-system (e.g., develop, regulate, provide and use digital health innovation).",
    "Archetypes displayed in bold represent main stakeholder type, while stakeholder sub-categories belonging to these groups are displayed in normal font.",
    "be adopted and maintained.",
    "To this effect, business models that incorporate societal responsibility might showcase how overcoming known hurdles to access digital health tools can result in added commercial value (e.g., expanded customer base).",
    "A concrete example that participants discussed is business models that take digital divide into account: digital divide is the phenomenon that disadvantaged groups face barriers to access (e.g., lack of digital devices, network connection, digital literacy skills) and as a result cannot benefit from digital health in the same way as other stakeholders."
